-- AgriBank, Jiangling Motors, PetroChina: China Equity Preview
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-03T00:32:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/agricultural-bank-vantone-petrochina-china-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
 unusual  price changes in China trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the last close.  The  Shanghai Composite Index , which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, dropped 8.59, or 0.3 percent, to
3,045.43. The  CSI 300 Index  fell 0.3 percent to 3,463.13.  Agricultural Bank of China Ltd.  (601288 CH): China’s
largest lender to farmers signed a letter of intent to lend
China Water Investment Co. 10 billion yuan ($1.5 billion) over
five years, China Business News reported, citing the bank. The
shares fell 0.4 percent to 2.77 yuan.  Beijing Vantone Real Estate Co.  (600246 CH): The property
developer has formed a 50-50 residential real estate venture
with China Ping An Trust & Investment Co., in which the trust
company will invest 5 billion yuan over five years. The stock
gained 2.6 percent to 6.80 yuan.  China Shipping Container Lines Co.  (601866 CH): The
country’s second-largest carrier of sea-cargo boxes had its Hong
Kong-listed shares raised to “buy” from “sell” at Citigroup
Inc. The stock jumped the 10 percent daily limit to 4.83 yuan.  Jiangling Motors Corp.  (000550 CH): The Chinese commercial
vehicle partner with Ford Motor Co. said vehicle sales in
October rose 52 percent from a year earlier to 14,118 units.
Production rose 40 percent to 13,058 units, it said. The stock
slid 3.6 percent to 31.42 yuan.       Luxi Chemical Group Co.  (000830 CH): The chemical company
said it has won approval from the China Securities Regulatory
Commission for an offering of 427 million new shares in a
private placement. The stock dropped 3.2 percent to 6.88 yuan.  PetroChina Co.  (601857 CH): The company said 157.5 billion
shares held by parent  China National Petroleum Corp . will become
tradable on Nov. 8. The shares rose 0.1 percent to 11.40 yuan.  Zhengzhou Yutong Bus Co.  (600066 CH): The bus maker’s
vehicle sales were 2,887 units last month. For 10 months, sales
were 31,066 units, an increase of 52 percent, it said. Zhengzhou
Yutong fell 3.3 percent to 23.46 yuan.  -- Zhang Shidong , William Bi. Editor:  Glenn J. Kalinoski   To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
